        <section id="athletics">
            <h5>Athletics</h5>
            <p>UA Little Rock's 14 athletic teams are known as the Little Rock Trojans, participating in the Sun Belt Conference. Notably, the university does not sponsor football. The main athletic offices are located in the Jack Stephens Center. Offered sports include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Baseball: A bat-and-ball game played between two teams of nine players each.</li>
                <li>Men's and Women's Basketball: A team sport where two teams try to score points by shooting a ball through the opposing team's hoop. </li>
                <li>Men's and Women's Golf: A sport in which players use clubs to hit a ball into a series of holes on a course in as few strokes as possible.</li>
                <li>Women's Volleyball: A team sport in which two teams of six players each try to score points by hitting a ball over a net.</li>
                <li>Women's Soccer: A team sport where two teams of eleven players aim to score goals by getting a ball into the opposing team's net.</li>
                <li>Women's Swimming/Diving: A competitive water sport involving various swimming styles and diving techniques.</li>
                <li>Men's and Women's Cross Country: A long-distance running sport where teams compete over natural terrain.</li>
                <li>Men's and Women's Track and Field (Indoor and Outdoor): A collection of athletic events including running, jumping, and throwing.</li>
                <li>Men's Wrestling: A combat sport where two competitors wrestle in a ring, using various techniques to gain points or pin the opponent.</li>
            </ul>
        </section> <!-- Closing section: athletics -->

